    "description": {
      "value": "<em>The goddess Sarenrae welcomes all who seek good in the world into her fold, and some goblins are drawn to worship her, in part due to her incarnation as a giant ball of fire.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Goblin, worshipper of Sarenrae.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>If the sun is visible, you can spend 1 round performing a wild dance in worship of the Dawnflower. Starting at the beginning of your next turn, allies who can see you gain a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls, skill checks, and saving throws. This effect lasts for a number of rounds equal to half your character level + your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1 round). At 9th level, this bonus increases to +2.",
